<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer12153234400347757207">A British &quot;fantastic fiction&quot; writer. He is fond of describing his work as &quot;weird fiction&quot; (after early 20th century pulp and horror writers such as H. P. Lovecraft), and belongs to a loose group of writers sometimes called New Weird who consciously attempt to move fantasy away from commercial, genre clichés of Tolkien epigons. He is also active in left-wing politics as a member of the Socialist W</span>
  <span id="freeText12153234400347757207" style="display:none">A British "fantastic fiction" writer. He is fond of describing his work as "weird fiction" (after early 20th century pulp and horror writers such as H. P. Lovecraft), and belongs to a loose group of writers sometimes called New Weird who consciously attempt to move fantasy away from commercial, genre clichés of Tolkien epigons. He is also active in left-wing politics as a member of the Socialist Workers Party. He has stood for the House of Commons for the Socialist Alliance, and published a book on Marxism and international law.<br /><br /><i>Excerpted from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Mi%C3%A9ville" rel="nofollow noopener">Wikipedia</a>.</i></span>
